SIMPLE: immediately
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immediately
<hw>Im*me"di*ate*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>In an immediate manner; without intervention of any other person or
thing; proximately; directly; -- opposed to <ant>mediately</ant>;
<as>as, <ex>immediately</ex> contiguous</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God's acceptance of it either <qex>immediately</qex> by himself,
or mediately by the hands of the bishop.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without interval of time; without delay; promptly;
instantly; at once.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And Jesus . . . touched him, saying, I will; be thou clean. And
<qex>immediately</qex> his leprosy was cleansed.</q> <rj><qau>Matt.
viii. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>As soon as. Cf. <er>Directly</er>, 8,
Note.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Directly; instantly; quickly; forthwith;
straightway; presently. See <er>Directly</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immediateness</ent>⟦br⟧
